Label: Adverse Outcome Pathway (AOP)
Description: A sequence of causally linked biological events that lead from exposure to a harmful effect on health or the environment

Label: Key Event (KE)
Description: A measurable change in biological state that is essential for the progression from exposure to adverse outcome

Label: Key Event Relationship (KER)
Description: The causal linkage between two key events, describing how one event leads to another

Label: Biological Process
Description: A series of molecular and cellular events that occur in living organisms

Label: Organ Context
Description: The specific organ or organ system in which a key event occurs

Label: Cell Type Context
Description: The specific type of cell in which a key event takes place

Label: Chemical Identifier
Description: A unique code that identifies a specific chemical substance

Label: Chemical Information
Description: Data and knowledge about chemical substances and their properties

Label: CAS Registry Number
Description: A unique numerical identifier assigned to chemical substances by the Chemical Abstracts Service

Label: InChI
Description: International Chemical Identifier - a textual representation of chemical structure

Label: InChIKey
Description: A hashed version of InChI providing a fixed-length identifier

Label: PubChem Compound ID
Description: An identifier for chemical compounds in the PubChem database

Label: ChEBI Identifier
Description: An identifier from the Chemical Entities of Biological Interest database

Label: SMILES
Description: Simplified Molecular Input Line Entry System - a text notation for chemical structures

Label: Taxonomic Classification
Description: The scientific classification of organisms into hierarchical groups

Label: Gene Identifier
Description: A unique code identifying a specific gene

Label: Protein Identifier
Description: A unique code identifying a specific protein

Label: Pathway Identifier
Description: A unique code identifying a biological pathway

Label: Disease or Disorder
Description: An abnormal condition affecting the body or mind

Label: Has Molecular Initiating Event
Description: Links an AOP to the initial interaction between a chemical and a biological system

Label: Has Key Event
Description: Links an AOP to one of its component key events

Label: Has Adverse Outcome
Description: Links an AOP to the final harmful effect at the individual or population level

Label: Has Key Event Relationship
Description: Links an AOP to a causal relationship between two of its key events

Label: Has Upstream Key Event
Description: Identifies the earlier event in a key event relationship

Label: Has Downstream Key Event
Description: Identifies the later event in a key event relationship

Label: Has Chemical Entity
Description: Links an AOP or key event to a chemical that can trigger or influence it

Label: Has Evidence
Description: Links to scientific evidence supporting an AOP or key event relationship

Label: Label
Description: A human-readable name for an entity

Label: Title
Description: The name or heading of an AOP or key event

Label: Description
Description: Detailed information explaining an entity

Label: Creator
Description: The person or organization that developed the AOP

Label: Identifier
Description: A unique code or number for the entity

Label: Created
Description: The date when the AOP was first created

Label: Modified
Description: The date when the AOP was last updated
